Episode 13 - Proving Ground screenplay 


Original Air Date: March 8, 2002

While training Air Force cadets at a top-secret facility, Colonel O\&#039;Neill 
learns of a possible alien incursion at Stargate Command. Knowing that other SG 
teams may be compromised, he has no choice but to take his young troops into a 
very real and very dangerous battle situation.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Episode 14 - 48 Hours screenplay 


Original Air Date: March 15, 2002

As the SG-1 team travels to Earth through the stargate, Teal\&#039;c is lost in 
transit, failing to materialize at Earth\&#039;s gate. Carter tries to figure out a 
way to bring him back safely. Meanwhile, Daniel negotiates with the Russians 
for their help, and O\&#039;Neill uses his own sources to try and find the answer.

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Episode 15 - Summit

Original Air Date: March 22, 2002

The Tok\&#039;ra learn that the Goa\&#039;uld System Lords are negotiating an alliance, 
and request Daniel Jackson\&#039;s help to infiltrate the meeting. Meanwhile, the 
other members of SG-1 help the Tok\&#039;ra to evacuate their base, and Samantha 
Carter makes a surprising discovery. (Part 1 of 2).

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Episode 16 - Last Stand screenplay 


Original Air Date: March 29, 2002

With time running out to complete his plans to release the biological weapon 
supplied by the Tok\&#039;ra, Daniel Jackson is confronted by Osiris, and he must come 
up with a new plan. At the same time, an attack force led by a mysterious 
Goa\&#039;uld approaches the Tok\&#039;ra home planet. (Part 2 of 2).
